          <div class="l">Satisfaction rate</div>
          <div class="d">From verified RezumFit users</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       ARTIFACT — the document on the left, JD + score on the right
       ============================================================ -->
  <section data-screen-label="03 Artifact">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sect-head">
        <div class="index">01 / Live preview</div>
        <h2>One resume, <em>recast</em><br>for every role.</h2>
        <p>Paste the listing on the right; watch your resume rewrite itself on the left. Keywords surface, language sharpens, dates align — without losing the voice that made it yours.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="artifact-wrap">
        <article class="artifact" aria-label="Sample tailored resume">
          <div class="topline">
            <div>
              <div class="name">Adaeze Eze</div>
              <div class="role">Senior Product Designer · Lagos / Remote</div>
            </div>
            <div class="right">
              adaeze.eze@mail<br>
              +234 · 803 · 555 · 0144<br>
              adaeze.studio
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Summary</h3>
          <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.55;color:#2a2926;font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-weight:300;font-variation-settings:'opsz' 24">
            Designer of enterprise tooling with eight years shipping calm, considered software for technical users. Comfortable holding the pen from discovery through ship; happiest at the seam between research and craft.
          </p>

          <h3>Experience</h3>
          <div class="entry">
            <div class="when">2023 — Now</div>
            <div class="what">
              <b>Lead Product Designer</b><i>Quill — developer infrastructure</i>
              <p>Owned the design of workflow primitives used by 14k engineers daily. Reduced time-to-first-deploy by 41%. Mentored two designers; partnered weekly with eng + research.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="entry">
            <div class="when">2020 — 2023</div>
            <div class="what">
              <b>Senior Designer</b><i>Northwind Labs</i>
              <p>Led the redesign of the data-modelling canvas. Authored a component system adopted across four product lines.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="entry">
            <div class="when">2017 — 2020</div>
            <div class="what">
              <b>Product Designer</b><i>Folio (acquired)</i>
              <p>Founding designer. From zero to 60k MAU. Designed the editor, the marketplace, and the brand.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <h3>Selected Skills</h3>
          <p style="font-family:'Inter Tight';font-size:13px;color:#3a3833;line-height:1.6">
            Systems design · Prototyping · Workflow modelling · Research synthesis · Figma · Code-aware design · Design ops
          </p>
        </article>

        <aside class="artifact-side">
          <div class="jd-card">
            <div class="label"><span>Job listing · pasted</span><span class="live">Analyzing</span></div>
            <div class="title">Lead Product Designer</div>
            <div class="co">Conduit, Inc. · Remote — North America</div>
            <div class="keywords">
              <span class="kw matched">Workflow design</span>
              <span class="kw matched">Enterprise</span>
              <span class="kw matched">Component systems</span>
              <span class="kw matched">Cross-functional</span>
              <span class="kw">B2B SaaS</span>
              <span class="kw matched">Mentorship</span>
              <span class="kw">0→1</span>
              <span class="kw matched">Research-led</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="score-card">
            <div class="num">94<sub>/100</sub></div>
            <div class="meta">
              <b>ATS fit score</b>
              <p>Strong match on craft & seniority. We surfaced three buried wins from your draft and rewrote your summary to lead with workflow tooling.</p>
              <div class="bar"><i></i></div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="jd-card" style="background:transparent;border-style:dashed">
            <div class="label"><span>What changed</span><span style="color:var(--accent)">+ 11 edits</span></div>
            <ul style="list-style:none;margin:14px 0 0;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px;font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:14px;font-weight:300;line-height:1.4">
              <li><span class="mono" style="color:var(--accent)">REWRITE</span> &nbsp; Summary now leads with <i>enterprise tooling</i></li>
              <li><span class="mono" style="color:var(--accent)">SURFACE</span> &nbsp; Mentorship, previously buried in row 3</li>
              <li><span class="mono" style="color:var(--accent)">METRIC</span> &nbsp; Pulled "41% faster deploys" forward</li>
              <li><span class="mono" style="color:var(--graphite)">KEEP</span> &nbsp; Voice. Cadence. The em-dashes.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       PERKS — what you get free
       ============================================================ -->
  <section data-screen-label="04 Perks">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sect-head">
        <div class="index">02 / What you get free</div>
        <h2>Start <em>free.</em><br>No strings attached.</h2>
        <p>Every account comes loaded from day one — no credit card, no trial timer, no upsell ambush. Two credits, all the AI providers, real exports.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <span class="num mono">Perk 01</span>
          <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">┌──────────────┐
│ <span class="acc">credits: 2</span>   │
│ status: live │
└──────────────┘</pre>
          </div>
          <h4>Two free <em>credits</em>.</h4>
          <p>No card needed. Upload your resume and start optimizing immediately — no friction between you and a working draft.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="num mono">Perk 02</span>
          <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">  GPT-4    <span class="acc">●</span>
  Claude   <span class="acc">●</span>
  Gemini   <span class="acc">●</span>
  → best-of-each</pre>
          </div>
          <h4>Three frontier <em>models</em>.</h4>
          <p>GPT-4, Claude, and Gemini — included on every account. We route each task to the model that handles it best, automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="num mono">Perk 03</span>
          <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">  resume.<span class="acc">pdf</span>   ↓
  resume.<span class="acc">docx</span>  ↓
  cover.<span class="acc">pdf</span>    ↓</pre>
          </div>
          <h4>PDF &amp; DOCX <em>exports</em>.</h4>
          <p>Download in any format. Free users included. Formatting and typography are preserved end-to-end — no broken layouts, ever.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="num mono">Perk 04</span>
          <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">  bought:    ████
  expires:   <span class="acc">never</span>
  use when:  ready</pre>
          </div>
          <h4>Credits don't <em>expire</em>.</h4>
          <p>Use them whenever you're ready. No monthly counter to remember, no rush, no pressure. Buy ten — use one a year if you want.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="num mono">Perk 05</span>
          <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">  upload    ↓
  paste JD  ↓
  download  <span class="acc">✓</span></pre>
          </div>
          <h4>Under <em>30</em> seconds.</h4>
          <p>From paste to polished, on a typical resume. The first draft is on screen before you've finished your coffee.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <span class="num mono">Perk 06</span>
          <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">  ATS engines:
   workday  <span class="acc">✓</span>
   greenhouse <span class="acc">✓</span>
   lever     <span class="acc">✓</span></pre>
          </div>
          <h4>Real ATS <em>checks</em>.</h4>
          <p>We score readability against the major ATS engines and flag anything brittle before you send. No surprises in the recruiter inbox.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       HOW IT WORKS
       ============================================================ -->
  <section id="how-it-works" data-screen-label="05 How it works">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sect-head">
        <div class="index">03 / How it works</div>
        <h2>Three quiet steps.<br><em>One</em> sharp document.</h2>
        <p>No magic, no melodrama. RezumFit is a careful editor — not a generator — that respects what's already on the page.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <span class="num mono">Step 01</span>
        <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">┌─────────────────────┐
│  resume.pdf      ⤴  │
│  cover_v3.docx   ⤴  │
│  <span class="acc">linkedin.json    ✓</span>  │
└─────────────────────┘</pre>
        </div>
        <h4>Bring what you <em>already</em> have.</h4>
        <p>Drop a PDF, a DOCX, a LinkedIn export — even a half-finished draft. We read structure, not just words.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <span class="num mono">Step 02</span>
        <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">                ┌──────────────┐
   listing  ──▶ │  <span class="acc">tailor()</span>     │ ──▶ draft
                └──────────────┘
   "we're looking for someone who..."
        ↳ <span class="acc">match: workflow, B2B, mentor</span></pre>
        </div>
        <h4>Paste the listing. We do the <em>reading</em>.</h4>
        <p>RezumFit identifies what the role actually rewards — then re-orders, rewrites, and re-emphasises with surgical restraint.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <span class="num mono">Step 03</span>
        <div class="ill">
<pre class="diagram">  draft.v07 ──▶  <span class="acc">[ you, editing ]</span>  ──▶ final
       ▲                  │
       └──────  redo ◀────┘
            "make it warmer"</pre>
        </div>
        <h4>Edit in plain <em>English</em>.</h4>
        <p>"Make it warmer." "Cut the jargon." "Lead with the metric." Type the note; the document obliges. You're always editor-in-chief.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       WHY NOT JUST USE CHATGPT?
       ============================================================ -->
  <section data-screen-label="06 vs ChatGPT">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sect-head">
        <div class="index">04 / vs ChatGPT</div>
        <h2>"Can't I just use <em>ChatGPT</em>?"</h2>
        <p>You could. But here's what that actually looks like — and why most candidates abandon the prompt-engineering approach by application three.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1px;background:color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink) 12%, transparent);border:1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink) 12%, transparent);border-radius:8px;overflow:hidden" class="vs-grid">
        <!-- ChatGPT side (paper) -->
        <div style="background:var(--paper);padding:40px 32px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px">
          <div>
            <span class="mono" style="color:var(--muted)">Option A</span>
            <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:28px;letter-spacing:-0.02em;font-weight:400;font-variation-settings:'opsz' 36;margin-top:8px">The ChatGPT way<em style="font-style:italic;color:var(--muted)">.</em></h3>
            <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;margin-top:6px">Manual, fragmented, time-consuming.</p>
          </div>
          <ul style="list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.5;padding:0;margin:0;border-top:1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink) 12%, transparent);padding-top:20px">
            <% [
              ["Write a detailed prompt", "15 min crafting the right instructions"],
              ["Copy-paste your resume", "Format gets destroyed in the process"],
              ["Copy-paste the job description", "Hope it understands the context"],
              ["Ask for keyword analysis", "Separate prompt, separate conversation"],
              ["Ask for a cover letter", "Another prompt, more copy-pasting"],
              ["Format everything yourself", "Back to Word/Docs to rebuild layout"],
              ["No ATS score", "Zero idea if it'll pass screening"],
              ["Repeat for every job", "Start from scratch each time"]
            ].each do |step, detail| %>
              <li style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr;gap:14px;align-items:start">
                <span class="mono" style="color:var(--graphite);padding-top:2px">·</span>
                <div>
                  <b style="font-weight:500;color:var(--ink)"><%= step %></b>
                  <span style="display:block;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;margin-top:2px"><%= detail %></span>
                </div>
              </li>
            <% end %>
          </ul>
          <div style="margin-top:auto;padding-top:20px;border-top:1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink) 12%, transparent);display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline">
            <span class="mono" style="color:var(--muted)">Total / application</span>
            <span style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:32px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-0.02em;font-variation-settings:'opsz' 60">45<em style="font-style:italic;color:var(--graphite)">+ min</em></span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- RezumFit side (ink dark) -->
        <div style="background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper);padding:40px 32px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px;position:relative">
          <div style="position:absolute;top:-1px;right:24px;background:var(--accent);color:#fff;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:6px 12px;border-radius:0 0 4px 4px">Recommended</div>
          <div>
            <span class="mono" style="color:color-mix(in oklab, var(--paper) 60%, transparent)">Option B</span>
            <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:28px;letter-spacing:-0.02em;font-weight:400;font-variation-settings:'opsz' 36;margin-top:8px;color:var(--paper)">The RezumFit way<em style="font-style:italic;color:var(--accent)">.</em></h3>
            <p style="color:color-mix(in oklab, var(--paper) 65%, transparent);font-size:13px;margin-top:6px">Automated, instant, professional.</p>
          </div>
          <ul style="list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.5;padding:0;margin:0;border-top:1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--paper) 14%, transparent);padding-top:20px">
            <% [
              ["Upload your resume", "PDF, DOCX, or paste — we parse it"],
              ["Paste the job description", "AI extracts every keyword automatically"],
              ["Get your ATS score instantly", "See where you stand: 34% → 89%"],
              ["One-click optimization", "Rewrites for maximum ATS compatibility"],
              ["Cover letter included", "Tailored to the job, ready to send"],
              ["Download DOCX & PDF", "Professional formatting preserved"],
              ["AI Pitch Deck generator", "12 investor slides in 60 seconds"],
              ["Track all applications", "Dashboard with status, follow-ups, scores"]
            ].each do |step, detail| %>
              <li style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr;gap:14px;align-items:start">
                <span class="mono" style="color:var(--accent);padding-top:2px">✓</span>
                <div>
                  <b style="font-weight:500;color:var(--paper)"><%= step %></b>
                  <span style="display:block;color:color-mix(in oklab, var(--paper) 60%, transparent);font-size:13px;margin-top:2px"><%= detail %></span>
                </div>
              </li>
            <% end %>
          </ul>
          <div style="margin-top:auto;padding-top:20px;border-top:1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--paper) 14%, transparent);display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:baseline">
            <span class="mono" style="color:color-mix(in oklab, var(--paper) 60%, transparent)">Total / application</span>
            <span style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:32px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-0.02em;font-variation-settings:'opsz' 60;color:var(--paper)"><em style="font-style:italic;color:var(--accent)">&lt;30</em>s</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center;padding:48px 0 24px">
        <p style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif;font-size:20px;font-weight:300;color:var(--muted);max-width:46ch;margin:0 auto 24px;line-height:1.45;font-style:italic">ChatGPT is a blank canvas. RezumFit is the finished document.</p>
        <%= link_to new_user_registration_path, class: "btn-primary" do %>
          Try it free — no prompt engineering
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <style>
      @media (max-width: 960px){ .editorial .vs-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr !important} }
    </style>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       MID-PAGE CTA
       ============================================================ -->
  <section data-screen-label="07 Mid CTA" style="padding:48px 0">
    <div class="wrap" style="text-align:center;border-block:1px solid color-mix(in oklab, var(--ink) 12%, transparent);padding:64px 0">
      <span class="mono" style="color:var(--accent)">Ready to begin</span>
